{
  "texts": [
    "In the case of B → K * τ + τ -only an upper limit is known: B( B0 → K * 0 τ + τ -) < 3.1×10 -3.",
    "In the ABCD model the result for B( B0 → K * 0 µ + µ -) encompasses the experimental interval.",
    "Requiring that it lies in the measured range, the predictions B( B0 → K * 0 τ + τ -) = (8.6 ± 1.3) × 10 -8 and B( B0 → K * 0 τ + τ -) = (8.6 ± 0.9) × 10 -8 are obtained for M Z ′ = 1 and 3 TeV, respectively.",
    "For the SM we have:B( B0 → K * 0 µ + µ -) = (9.6 ± 2.0) × 10 -7 (|λ * ts |/0.04) 2 and B( B0 → K * 0 τ + τ -) = (9.2 ± 2.0) × 10 -8 (|λ *ts |/0.04) 2.",
    "The B → K * (Kπ)µ + µ -angular distribution has been experimentally studied in details [77][78][79][80][81][82][83][84], finding a deviation from SM predictions in some angular P -observables defined in (57) [50,[85][86][87][88][89][90]."
  ]
}